The '''Bank of Natural Capital''' is an educational initiative associated with [[The Economics of Ecosystems and Biodiversity]] (TEEB) to communicate [[natural capital]] investment and [[value theory]] related to what are sometimes called "[[Social capital|economic intangibles]]" to the global public, in particular the direct economic and financial value of [[ecosystem services]] to man.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bankofnaturalcapital.com|title=Bank of natural – Capital|website=bankofnaturalcapital.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sustainableprosperityproject.com/article320 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2010-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716170146/http://www.sustainableprosperityproject.com/article320 |archive-date=2011-07-16 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

It encapsulates the idea that the natural world is defined as capital and something to profit on through a capitalist society, saying 'we pay for things we find valuable'. The capitalist construction of nature as something with a value will lead to, as already apparent its over-abstraction and system collapse. 

