{{Expand French|Direct Énergie|topic=energy|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox company| | name = Direct Énergie | logo = | type = [[S.A. (corporation)|Société Anonyme]] | traded_as = | location_city = [[Paris]] | location_country = [[France]] | foundation = {{Start date and years ago|2003|03|}} | industry = [[Electric utility]] | predecessor = | products = [[Natural gas]] distribution, [[electricity generation]] and [[electricity distribution|distribution]], [[wind power]] | revenue = {{increase}}[[Euro|€]]1.692 billion <small>(2016)</small> | net_income = €123.6 million <small>(2016)</small> | assets = | equity = €2.020 billion <small>(2016)</small> | num_employees = 416 <small>(2016)</small> | key_people = Xavier Caïtucoli <small>([[CEO]])</small> | homepage = [http://www.direct-energie.com direct-energie.com] | owner = {{ubl|[[Impala SAS]] (34,51 %) | AMS Industries (19,39 %) | [[Luxempart]] (10,03 %) | [[EBM (Société coopérative Elektra Birseck)|EbM]] (9,97 %) | LOV Group Invest (5,92 %) | Direction (5,71 %) | Self-owned (0,43 %)<ref name="Actionnariat">{{cite web |title=Notre organisation - Actionnariat |url=http://groupe.direct-energie.com/qui-sommes-nous/notre-organisation/actionnariat/ |website=Direct Énergie |access-date=28 May 2017|language=French}}</ref>|}} }} '''Direct Énergie''' is a [[France|French]] international [[electric utility]] company, which operates in the fields of [[electricity generation]] and [[electric distribution|distribution]], [[natural gas]], and [[renewable energy]]. Founded in France in 2003 as an alternative to the historic monopoly [[Électricité de France]], it is present in [[Belgium]] through the subsidiary Poweo.
== Activities == The group produces electricity and serves 2.1 millions consumers<ref>{{cite web|date=January 17, 2017|title=Direct Energie targets 4 mln clients in France by 2020|author=Geert De Clercq, Benjamin Mallet, and Richard Balmforth|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/direct-energie-france-power-idUSL5N1F74TP|website=reuters.com|accessdate=6 August 2017}}</ref> in France and Belgium, both in retail and company-oriented market.<ref name="DdR2016">{{Cite web |title=Document de référence 2016 |url=http://groupe.direct-energie.com/fileadmin/Metiers/Groupe/Investisseurs/rapports_annuels/2017/DE_Document_de_reference_2016_-__version_visee_.pdf |format=pdf |website=groupe.direct-energie.com |date=2017 |access-date=28 May 2017|language=French}}</ref> It handles 800 MW of electricity production capacity, mainly [[gas power station]]s.<ref name=challengesQuadran>{{cite web|url=https://www.challenges.fr/entreprise/energie/pourquoi-direct-energie-investit-dans-les-renouvelables-en-reprenant-quadran_480733|title=Pourquoi Direct Energie investit dans les renouvelables|date=16 June 2017|access-date=16 June 2017|website=challenges.fr|language=French}}</ref>
== History == Founded in 2003, Direct Énergie made no profit in serving the corporate market nor the household market during its first years of existence. In 2008 is founded [[Neoen]], a subsidiary dedicated to build and operate [[renewable energy|renewable]] [[power station]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/societes/2015/02/06/20005-20150206ARTFIG00319-neoen-deploie-ses-eoliennes-en-australie.php|title= Neoen déploie ses éoliennes en Australie|author=Frédéric De Monicault|date=6 February 2015|accessdate=29 July 2017|website=lefigaro.fr|language=fr}}</ref>
The group bought 46% of its competitor {{ill|Poweo|fr}} in 2011,<ref>{{cite web|title=Direct Energie prend le contrôle de Poweo|date=1 October 2011|author=Jean-Michel Bezat|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/economie/article/2011/10/01/direct-energie-prend-le-controle-de-poweo_1580887_3234.html|access-date=29 July 2017|language=French|website=lemonde.fr}}</ref> before merging the following year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Poweo Direct Energie : naissance du 3ème opérateur d'énergie français |url=https://www.challenges.fr/entreprise/poweo-direct-energie-naissance-du-3eme-operateur-d-energie-francais_7311 |website=Challenges.fr |date=12 July 2012 |accessdate=28 May 2017|language=French}}</ref>
In April 2018, the French energy major [[Total S.A.]] claims they are buying 74% of Direct Énergie capital from their main stockholders, for 1,4 billion euros.<ref>{{cite web|language=fr|title=Total va acheter Direct Energie et espère bousculer le marché de l’électricité|author= Nabil Wakim|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/energies/article/2018/04/18/total-va-acheter-74-de-direct-energie-pour-1-4-milliard-d-euros_5286891_1653054.html|website=Le Monde.fr|accessdate=2018-04-18|date=2018-04-18}}</ref>
== Sponsoring == Direct Énergie was a partner of the [[Olympique de Marseille]] from 2008 to 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|language=French|title=OM / Direct Énergie : Le bilan de 2 ans de partenariat |url=https://www.om.net/actualites/139909/om-direct-energie-le-bilan-de-2-ans-de-partenariat |website=om.net|date=12 May 2010 |access-date=4 June 2017}}</ref> The company has been the main sponsor of a French [[Direct Énergie (cycling team)|pro cycling team]] since 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|language=French|title=Europcar devient Direct Énergie|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Cyclisme-sur-route/Actualites/Europcar-devient-direct-energie/590584 |website=lequipe.fr|date=15 September 2015 |access-date=1 August 2017}}</ref>
