[[File:Osaka Castle Sakuramon Kyoseki2.jpg|thumb|Octopus stone]]
The '''octopus stone''', ''Taiko-ishi'' 蛸石 (also called "Drum Rock") is a large stone at [[Osaka Castle]] in Japan. The stone is near Sakura Gate.{{sfn|Schmorleitz|1974|p=22}} It is one of the largest of several [[megalith]]s at the castle (by face area), at 5.5×11.7 meters and over {{convert|120|tonne}}.{{sfn|Exploring the history of Osaka Castle|1992|p=80}}{{sfn|Lee|1993|p=77}} Its name is derived from the octopus shape visible on its lower left corner.<ref>http://muza-chan.net/japan/index.php/blog/osaka-castle-giant-stones</ref>

