'''Raum Energy Inc.''' was a company based in [[Saskatoon]], Saskatchewan, Canada which designed and manufactured small-scale [[wind turbine]]s, grid-tie inverter and battery charge controller systems. These systems, which could run off of either wind or photovoltaic generated power, were specifically designed for use with residential-scale applications. The company's 1.3&nbsp;kW turbine was one of the first systems setup for testing at [[Canada]]'s Wind Energy Institute for to participate in a national study into the reliability and performance of small-scale generator systems.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.weican.ca/news/2008/080925-WEICan-begins-first-testing-program-with-Raum.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090611133308/http://www.weican.ca/news/2008/080925-WEICan-begins-first-testing-program-with-Raum.php |archivedate=2009-06-11 |df= }}</ref>
The company's flagship system combined a 3.5&nbsp;kW turbine with a grid-tie inverter or battery charge controller and could generate 6,000&nbsp;kW-hrs of energy annually.<ref>http://www2.canada.com/saskatoonstarphoenix/news/business/story.html?id=aebde93e-28a6-4f7f-8b53-51f64357a287</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.raumenergy.com/3.5kW_Spec_Sheet.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715155147/http://www.raumenergy.com/3.5kW_Spec_Sheet.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-15 |df= }}</ref> This system was set to also begin testing at WEICAN in April 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.weican.ca/news/2010/100127-WEICan-Testing-Raum-3-5.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-03-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706212952/http://www.weican.ca/news/2010/100127-WEICan-Testing-Raum-3-5.php |archivedate=2011-07-06 |df= }}</ref>
Raum Energy Inc. was awarded the 2009 Western [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[National Research Council (Canada)|National Research Council]]'s award for innovative new technology.<ref>http://www.tvp-ii.org/english/awards.asp</ref>
