{{Unreferenced|date=September 2009}}
A '''tubing hanger''' is a component used in the completion of [[oil]] and [[gas]] production wells.  It is set in the [[Christmas tree (oil well)|tree]] or the [[wellhead]] and suspends the [[production tubing]] and/or [[casing (oil well)|casing]].  Sometimes it provides porting to allow the communication of [[hydraulic]], [[electric]] and other downhole functions, as well as [[chemical]] injection. It also serves to seal-in the annulus and production areas.

==External links==
*[http://www.glossary.oilfield.slb.com/Display.cfm?Term=tubing%20hanger Schlumberger Oilfield Glossary: Tubing Hanger]

