{{Infobox Particle | bgcolour = | name = Upsilon ({{SubatomicParticle|Upsilon}}) | image = [[Image:Upsilon peak.jpg|150px]] | caption = A plot of the [[invariant mass]] of [[muon]] pairs, from the '''Upsilon particle''' discovery paper. The peak at about 9.5&nbsp;GeV is due to the contribution of the Upsilon meson. | num_types = | composition = {{SubatomicParticle|Bottom quark}}{{SubatomicParticle|Bottom antiquark}} | statistics = [[Bosonic]] | group = [[Hadron]]s | generation = | interaction = | particle = | antiparticle = Self | status = | theorized = | discovered = [[E288 experiment]] | symbol = {{SubatomicParticle|Upsilon}} | mass = {{val|9.46030|(26)|u=GeV/c2}} | decay_time = {{val|1.21|e=-20|ul=s}} | decay_particle = | electric_charge = 0 [[elementary charge|''e'']] | color_charge = | spin = 1 | num_spin_states = }}
The '''Upsilon meson''' ({{SubatomicParticle|Upsilon}}) is a [[quarkonium]] state (i.e. [[Flavour (particle physics)|flavourless]] [[meson]]) formed from a [[bottom quark]] and its [[antiparticle]]. It was discovered by the [[E288 experiment]] team, headed by [[Leon Lederman]], at [[Fermilab]] in 1977, and was the first particle containing a bottom quark to be discovered because it is the lightest that can be produced without additional massive particles. It has a [[mean lifetime|lifetime]] of {{val|1.21|e=-20|ul=s}} and a mass about {{val|9.46|ul=GeV/c2}} in the ground state.
==See also== * [[Oops-Leon]], an erroneously-claimed discovery of a similar particle at a lower mass in 1976. * The {{SubatomicParticle|link=yes|Phi meson}} particle is the analogous state made from [[strange quark]]s. * The {{SubatomicParticle|link=yes|J/Psi}} particle is the analogous state made from [[charm quark]]s. * [[List of mesons]]
